cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on face recognition accuracy in Computer Vision systems, which is a core topic in the Computer Vision field. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning and statistical-based face recognition, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes novel models, which can be considered as a machine learning approach, and hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the factors affecting the accuracy of face recognition, which can be related to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
